			<div id="post-1802" class="post-1802 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-survival-preparedness tag-camping tag-first-aid tag-kids tag-tents tag-wild-life tag-wild-plants tag-wilderness-skills">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/survival-knowledge-camping" title="Permalink to Episode-426- Developing Survival Knowledge While Camping" rel="bookmark">Episode-426- Developing Survival Knowledge While Camping</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				 <span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/survival-knowledge-camping" title="10:12 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">April 28, 2010</span></a> <span class="byline"><span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/author/Modern Survival" title="View all posts by Modern Survival">Modern Survival</a></span></span><span class="comments-link"><span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/survival-knowledge-camping#comments" title="Comment on Episode-426- Developing Survival Knowledge While Camping">16 Comments</a></span>
			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<div id="tweetbutton1802" class="tw_button" style="float:right;margin-left:10px;"><a href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Fsurvival-knowledge-camping&amp;text=Episode-426-%20Developing%20Survival%20Knowledge%20While%20Camping&amp;related=&amp;lang=en&amp;count=horizontal&amp;counturl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Fsurvival-knowledge-camping" class="twitter-share-button"  style="width:55px;height:22px;background:transparent url('http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-tweet-button/tweetn.png') no-repeat  0 0;text-align:left;text-indent:-9999px;display:block;">Tweet</a></div><div class="podPress_content podPress_content_audio_mp3">
<div class="podpress_playerspace podpress_playerspace_audio_mp3 podpress_mp3player" style="display:block;" ><div id="podPressPlayerSpace_3"><!-- podPress --></div></div>
<div class="podPress_downloadlinks podPress_downloadlinks_audio_mp3"><a href="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/4-10/epi-00426-survival-skill-development-while-camping.mp3" target="new" title="Download: Episode-426- Developing Survival Knowledge While Camping" class="podpress_downloadimglink podpress_downloadimglink_audio_mp3"><img src="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress/images/audio_mp3_button.png" class="podPress_imgicon podpress_imgicon_audio_mp3" alt="" /></a> <span class="podpress_mediafile_title podpress_mediafile_title_audio_mp3">Episode-426- Developing Survival Knowledge While Camping</span> <span class="podpress_mediafile_dursize podpress_mediafile_dursize_audio_mp3">[ 58:24 ]</span> <a href="#podPressPlayerSpace_3" class="podpress_playlink podpress_playlink_audio_mp3" onclick="javascript:podPressShowHidePlayer('3', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/4-10/epi-00426-survival-skill-development-while-camping.mp3', 290, 24, 'false', 'http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress//images/vpreview_center.png', 'Episode-426- Developing Survival Knowledge While Camping', 'The Survival Podcast'); return false;"><span id="podPressPlayerSpace_3_PlayLink" class="podPress_playerspace_playlink">Play Now</span></a><input type="hidden" id="podPressPlayerSpace_3_OrigURL" value="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/4-10/epi-00426-survival-skill-development-while-camping.mp3" /> | <a href="#podPressPlayerSpace_3" class="podpress_playinpopup podpress_playinpopup_audio_mp3" onclick="javascript:podPressPopupPlayer('3', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/4-10/epi-00426-survival-skill-development-while-camping.mp3', 290, 24, 'The Survival Podcast', '1802', 'Episode-426- Developing Survival Knowledge While Camping', 'The Survival Podcast'); return false;">Play in Popup</a> | <a href="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/4-10/epi-00426-survival-skill-development-while-camping.mp3" target="new" class="podpress_downloadlink podpress_downloadlink_audio_mp3">Download</a></div></div>
<script type="text/javascript">podPressShowHidePlayer('3', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/4-10/epi-00426-survival-skill-development-while-camping.mp3', 290, 24, 'false', 'http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress//images/vpreview_center.png', 'Episode-426- Developing Survival Knowledge While Camping', 'The Survival Podcast');</script><p>My view on survival planning is that running out into the forest to hide if the shit hits the fan is generally a very bad move, well in most situations.  Today though we are going to look at camping in another light.  When you camp you deal with out a lot of the conveniences we tend to take for granted, families communicate better (sometimes by force) and opportunities for leaning and contingency plan development present themselves.</p>
<p><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Join Me Today as we Discuss&#8230;</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>New MSB Supporting Vendor <a target="_blank" href="http://campingsurvival.com/" target="_blank">CampingSurvival.com</a> (MSB get 5% off all orders)</li>
<li>Camping to learn about survival vs. survival camping</li>
<li>Don&#8217;t go spend a lot of money right away</li>
<li>The basics
<ul>
<li>Good tents</li>
<li>Padding, air mattresses or cots</li>
<li>Lighting</li>
<li>Food &#8211; including some &#8220;healthy junk foods&#8221;</li>
<li>Insect repellent</li>
<li>A way to cook</li>
<li>First aid kit</li>
<li>Storage bins</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Start out close to home with full amenities</li>
<li>Focus on self reliance with shelter, food, water</li>
<li>Get away from the crowds even in crowded areas</li>
<li>Move on to more remote camping once you have a system in place</li>
<li>Purchase animal, insect, plant, bird, etc field guides and use them</li>
<li>Make fishing part of your camping experiences</li>
<li>Require children to deal with discomfort <span style="text-decoration: underline;">within reason</span></li>
<li>Take time to work on skill development (crafts, navigation, etc)</li>
<li>Use the time for bonding, it may be part of family survival some day</li>
<li>The golden rule, have fun and learn</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Additional Resources for     Today’s Show</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/members" target="_blank">Members      Support Brigade</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://store.survivalpodcast.net/" target="_blank">TSP Gear     Shop</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="../forum" target="_blank">Join     Our Forum</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.murs-radio.com/" target="_blank">MURS Radio</a> &#8211; (sponsor of the day)</li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://prepared.pro/" target="_blank">Safecastle Royal</a> &#8211; (sponsor of the day)</li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://survival.instantestore.net/cat-magazine.cfm" target="_blank">Ron Hood’s Survival.com Magazine</a></li>
</ul>
